Here is one of my PHP standards... I prefer this to more complex template systems, although the idea is borrowed from Symfony I think. The style I try to adhere to is to only use simple variables and loops in html templates.  This is the basic idea:<p>function render($data, $templateFile) {<p><pre><code>    extract( $data );
    ob_start();
    require $templateFile;
    echo ob_get_clean();
</code></pre>
}<p>It turns an array (or DTO object using get_object_vars) into  global variables in the template, so this code in a controller<p>$data->foo = "bar";<p>Is accessed in the template like this:<p><?= $foo ?>
